The paper discusses the use of machine learning and pattern recognition techniques for time series visualization, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for time series visualization, specifically using network metrics to characterize time series for classification. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper proposes a method to visualize time series as complex networks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks. 

cs.DM (Data Mining): The paper discusses the use of graph statistics to characterize time series for better visual exploration and statistical analysis, which could fall under the category of data mining. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for time series visualization, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of network metrics to characterize time series for classification, which could fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing.
